+
+# Amplified Partners Ops Audit and Future Framework
+
+## Evidence Tiers Used
+
+| Tier | Meaning in this report | Examples |
+|---|---|---|
+| MEASURED | Verified against live system metadata during the audit | Repo existence, default branches, archive status, open PR snapshot |
+| STRUCTURED | Found in prior brain/session research or explicit operating doctrine | GitHub/Linear/Vellum roles, Vellum write-authority rule, no-code-before-verification |
+| INFERRED | Consistent with evidence, but not explicitly specified | Agent commits only on feature branches, PR-first discipline where branch protection exists |
+| UNRESOLVED | Not found in live GitHub metadata or accessible prior research | Exact Cove-vs-Cursor rule, Beast deploy owner, exact branch naming pattern |
+
+## Current Source-of-Truth Map
+
+| System | Role | Current rule |
+|---|---|---|
+| GitHub | Source of truth for code, versioned docs, and approved policy artefacts | Treat repo HEAD and protected branches as the current code baseline |
+| Linear | Work ledger and coordination surface | Every commit or material change should link to a Linear ticket |
+| Vellum | Write-authority and governance outlet | Production writes and significant decisions require Vellum-style receipt or proceed/hold/revise/escalate packet |
+| Brain / MCP | Context, memory, and research substrate | Use it for discovery, then reset against current repo/runtime state |
+| Beast | Runtime/source-material host | Do not claim runtime truth without live verification |
+| Cursor / Cove / Devin | Implementation agents | Executor choice remains policy-dependent; reversible repo work is allowed only within fixed ceilings |
+| Perplexity | Research, critique, orchestration, and report synthesis | Can coordinate and verify, but should not bypass Vellum or production gates |
+
