+
+## Operating Framework for Future Work
+
+### Default Execution Loop
+
+1. State the plan before acting.
+2. Link the work to Linear or a session-pack ticket.
+3. Verify source-of-truth material before touching code.
+4. Do the smallest reversible step.
+5. Run the relevant checks.
+6. Write a Vellum-style receipt or handoff.
+7. Compare plan versus actual result.
+8. Record blockers, deltas, and next action.
+
+### Before Coding
+
+Every substantial implementation task should produce or update:
+
+- Source map verification (which repos, which branches, which runtime state)
+- Brain/prior-research reset (what was found, what is stale)
+- Contradictions and blockers log
+- Relevant ADRs where architecture is unresolved
+- First implementation ticket breakdown
+
+Do not code if the source map, runtime path, or architecture decision is unclear and material to the task.
+
+### Wide Blinkers, Fixed Ceilings
+
+**Allowed without re-asking (inside an agreed repo):**
+
+- Read-only Git/GitHub inspection
+- Local diffs, logs, branches, status, fetches
+- Tests, lint, type checks, builds, local validation
+- Installing project dependencies into project-local environments
+- Editing files on feature branches
+- Drafting docs in `03_shadow`, session packs, research folders, ADR drafts
+- Background research and parallel assessment agents
+
+**Always ask or escalate first:**
+
+- `git push`, `git push --force`, `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fd`
+- Commits (unless explicitly authorised)
+- Production SSH or destructive Docker operations
+- Database destructive writes
+- `.env`, credentials, IAM, or vault changes
+- Marketing sends, social posts, landing-page publishes, public content
+- `03_shadow` to `01_truth` promotion
+- P0 epistemic signoff
+- Any action touching secrets, PII, production, or external users
+
+## Product and Governance Gates
+
+| Gate | Rule |
+|---|---|
+| Marketing publish | No send/post/publish without approval, consent verification, and Vellum decision packet |
+| Brevo/email | SPF, DKIM, DMARC, suppression, consent source, and warm-up must be verified before real sends |
+| Synthetic content | Disclosure rules must be checked before publishing AI-generated testimonials, ads, case studies, or video |
+| `03_shadow` to `01_truth` | Human-held until explicit delegation exists |
+| P0 | Halt, log, escalate; no silent promotion or self-signoff |
+| Secrets | Never touch without explicit vault path and approval |
+| PII | Keep separate by design; no PII in logs, generated content, or marketing tables unless explicitly authorised and protected |
+
+## Architecture Decisions Still Open
+
+| Decision | Why it matters | ADR stub |
+|---|---|---|
+| Graph/vector layer | Conflicting signals across FalkorDB, Qdrant, Neo4j, PostgreSQL, Apache AGE, pgvector | `docs/adr/ADR-001-graph-vector-direction.md` |
+| Marketing-engine integration | Active TypeScript work may conflict with Python-first marketing implementation | `docs/adr/ADR-002-marketing-engine-integration.md` |
+| Executor routing (Cove vs Cursor vs Devin) | Prior research names different agents as primary executor in different contexts | `docs/adr/ADR-003-executor-routing.md` |
+| Beast deploy ownership | Runtime verification not established | `docs/adr/ADR-004-beast-deploy-ownership.md` |
+| Kaizen rename | `kaizen-surface-loop` not found as a repo | `docs/adr/ADR-005-kaizen-rename.md` |
+| Problem receipt location | Vellum receipt doctrine exists, exact file path/owner unresolved | `docs/adr/ADR-006-problem-receipt-location.md` |
+
+## Reusable Audit Template
+
+```text
+TIER:
+DATE:
+SCOPE:
+
+1. Live system snapshot (repos, branches, PRs, checks, runtime)
+2. Prior doctrine (source-of-truth rules, agent roles, gates, decisions)
