+
+# ADR-001: Graph/Vector Layer Direction
+
+## Status
+
+**Accepted.** Already decided and documented in `00_authority/DATA_ARCHITECTURE.md` v1 (Devon-973e, 2026-05-08) and Knowledge Note `note-17e5ce67451946879460475f6b9cecb2`.
+
+This ADR exists to close the loop flagged in the ops audit. The decision is made.
+
+## Decision
+
+PostgreSQL + Apache AGE (graph) + pgvector with HNSW indexing (vector). One database engine, three capabilities, no separate processes.
+
+## Deprecated
+
+- FalkorDB → replaced by Apache AGE
+- Qdrant → replaced by pgvector
+
+## Migration Status
+
+All migrations planned, not yet executed:
+- FalkorDB → AGE: 9,000 nodes across 4 graphs
+- Qdrant → pgvector: 57,434 embeddings (384-dim)
+- Token-proxy semantic cache → pgvector table
+
+## Consequences
+
+- No new work uses FalkorDB or Qdrant
+- Existing FalkorDB/Qdrant code is legacy — migrate or flag
+- `amplified-knowledge-mcp` needs updating to target AGE + pgvector
+
+---
+
+*Devon | 2026-05-24 | devin-bfbc7fe01e7c43dda8cbbb7f9d4a73ec*
