+
+# ADR-002: Marketing Engine Integration Direction
+
+## Status
+
+**Proposed.** Needs Ewan decision.
+
+## Context
+
+`marketing-engine` is an active TypeScript/Python repo with content generation, atomisation, and distribution pipelines. `amplified-machine/core` also has marketing-related routes and integrations (Brevo, Remotion, ElevenLabs). `crm/app/marketing_machine` has a third implementation.
+
+Three codebases touching marketing. Which is canonical?
+
+## Options
+
+1. **`marketing-engine` is canonical.** Port any unique features from `amplified-machine` and `crm` into it. Single repo for all marketing automation.
+2. **`amplified-machine` absorbs marketing.** Marketing-engine becomes a thin API client. Machine repo owns the pipeline.
+3. **Coexist with clear boundaries.** Marketing-engine owns content generation/distribution. CRM owns client-specific personalization. Machine owns orchestration. Define the API contracts between them.
+
+## Consequences
+
+Option 1: one codebase, simpler, but requires a migration.
+Option 2: bigger repo, more coupling, but single deployment.
+Option 3: most flexible, but requires explicit API contracts and avoids drift.
+
+## Open Questions
+
+- Which repo has the most recent working implementation?
+- Is the TypeScript work in marketing-engine ahead of the Python work in amplified-machine?
+- Does Ewan want to consolidate or keep separation?
+
+---
+
+*Devon | 2026-05-24 | devin-bfbc7fe01e7c43dda8cbbb7f9d4a73ec*
