+# ADR-004: Beast Deploy Ownership
+
+## Status
+
+**Proposed.** Needs runtime verification and Ewan decision.
+
+## Context
+
+Beast (`135.181.161.131`, Hetzner M5, 96 cores, 252GB RAM) hosts ~40 containers. Devon has SSH access via `beastkey`. But "who owns deploys" is unresolved:
+
+- Devon runs scheduled health checks (AMP-141, AMP-147)
+- Antigravity has agent directories on Beast (`/opt/amplified/antigravity/`)
+- Vellum is deployed to Beast (port 8400) — deployed by Devon in this session
+- `02_build/INFRASTRUCTURE.md` documents containers but not deploy ownership
+
+## Options
+
+1. **Devon owns all deploys.** Single point of coordination. All pushes to Beast go through Devon sessions.
+2. **Agent-owned services.** Each agent owns their service: Devon owns Vellum, Enforcer. AG owns the Machine. Ewan owns LiteLLM config.
+3. **Git-driven deploys.** Merge to main triggers deploy via GitHub Actions. No agent manually SSHs. Beast pulls from Git.
+
+## Consequences
+
+Option 1: simplest but creates a bottleneck on Devon sessions.
+Option 2: distributed but requires clear service ownership registry.
+Option 3: most robust but requires CI/CD pipeline to Beast (currently absent).
+
+---
+
