+
+# ADR-006: Problem Receipt Location
+
+## Status
+
+**Proposed.** Needs Ewan decision.
+
+## Context
+
+The ops audit and operating framework require a "Vellum-style receipt" for every unit of work. The receipt doctrine exists but the exact format, file path, and owner are unresolved.
+
+Receipts could live in:
+- **Vellum** — entries on the ledger (hash-chained, attributed, immutable)
+- **Linear** — ticket comments
+- **GitHub** — PR descriptions (plan-execution mirror)
+- **`clean-build/03_shadow/job-wrapups/`** — markdown files
+
+## Options
+
+1. **Vellum is canonical.** Every receipt is a Vellum entry. Linear and GitHub get links to the Vellum entry. Single source of truth.
+2. **Triple-write.** Receipt goes to Vellum, Linear, and GitHub. Redundant but visible everywhere.
+3. **GitHub PR is the receipt.** The plan-execution mirror in the PR description IS the receipt. Vellum gets a hash of the PR for audit chain.
+
+## Recommendation
+
+OPINION 80%: Option 1. Vellum is the governance surface — receipts belong there. Linear and GitHub are execution surfaces that link to the Vellum receipt. This is consistent with the source-of-truth map: Vellum = write-authority.
+
+## Receipt Format (Proposed)
+
+```json
+{
+    "entry_type": "decision",
+    "author": "<agent>",
+    "content": "<one-line summary of what was done>",
+    "epistemic_tier": "<tier of the work output>",
+    "metadata": {
+        "type": "receipt",
+        "linear_ticket": "AMP-NNN",
+        "github_pr": "org/repo#NN",
+        "plan_hash": "<sha256 of the plan>",
+        "execution_hash": "<sha256 of the execution log>",
+        "delta": "<one-line description of plan vs actual>"
+    }
+}
+```
+
+---
